\begin_layout Standard
Consider the following continuous time economy with a single final good,
 populated by a representative household with preferences over consumption
 and R&D labor 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\mathbb{E}_{t}\int_{t}^{\infty}\exp\left(-\rho\left(s-t\right)\right)\left(\ln C_{s}-\frac{\chi\left(L_{s}^{RD}\right)^{1+\frac{1}{\varphi}}}{1+\frac{1}{\varphi}}\right)\mathrm{d}s,\label{eq:Utility}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 is the Frisch labor supply.
 In addition, the representative household inelastically supplies 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 units of production labor.
