 growth.
 In this model, banning defensive innovation leads to a first-best where
 only entrants conduct R&D and reallocation does not hamper growth.
 However, such a ban might be impossible to implement, as determining the
 nature of patents ex-ante might in practice be unfeasible.
 For this reason, I assume that the planner cannot distinguish productive
 from unproductive projects, and can only employ using tax instruments.
